WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:05.771
[ stevie wonder's
"someday at christmas" plays ]

00:05.773 --> 00:10.943
♪ someday at christmas,
men won't be boys ♪

00:10.945 --> 00:16.048
♪ playing with bombs like kids
play with toys ♪

00:16.050 --> 00:20.185
♪ one warm December,
our hearts will see ♪

00:20.187 --> 00:24.723
♪ a world where men are free ♪

00:24.725 --> 00:30.662
♪ mm, someday at christmas,
there'll be no wars ♪

00:30.664 --> 00:35.734
♪ when we have learned
what christmas is for ♪

00:35.736 --> 00:39.705
♪ when we have found
what life's really worth ♪

00:39.707 --> 00:45.344
♪ there'll be peace on earth ♪

00:45.346 --> 00:50.215
♪ someday all our dreams
will come to be ♪

00:50.217 --> 00:54.820
♪ someday in a world
where men are free ♪

00:54.822 --> 00:58.690
♪ maybe not in time
for you and me ♪
I like that one.

00:58.692 --> 01:03.862
♪ but someday
at christmastime ♪

01:03.864 --> 01:07.199
♪ someday at christmas,
we'll see a land ♪
[ sighs ]

01:07.201 --> 01:09.001
What's harding's wife's
name again?

01:09.003 --> 01:11.403
Sandy.
Sandy. She's --

01:11.405 --> 01:13.572
Home and garden editor
at the<i> columbus tribune.</i>

01:13.574 --> 01:15.507
We need to pass this
spending bill, olivia.

01:15.509 --> 01:16.408
I know.

01:16.410 --> 01:18.210
♪ people will share ♪

01:18.212 --> 01:21.046
♪ a world where people care ♪

01:21.048 --> 01:22.848
Nog.

01:22.850 --> 01:24.716
You went nog.
I did.

01:24.718 --> 01:26.251
I got punch.

01:26.253 --> 01:27.886
To each their own.
Mm.

01:27.888 --> 01:29.555
When I took this job,

01:29.557 --> 01:31.090
I had no idea how many holiday
parties were involved.

01:31.092 --> 01:32.391
This is my last one
of the night.

01:32.393 --> 01:34.193
Well, cheers to that.
[ glasses clink ]

01:34.195 --> 01:36.562
You see that?
What?

01:36.564 --> 01:38.797
It looks like olivia pope,
it sounds like olivia pope,

01:38.799 --> 01:40.232
But that over there

01:40.234 --> 01:43.035
Making chitchat like
a trophy wife is weird.

01:43.037 --> 01:44.870
All I see
is a happy holiday.

01:44.872 --> 01:46.472
Our charm offensive's
working.

01:46.474 --> 01:47.639
Poll numbers are up,

01:47.641 --> 01:50.142
And america's starting
to fall for olivia pope.

01:50.144 --> 01:52.277
All I'm saying is,
don't get used to it.

01:52.279 --> 01:56.648
I just feel like I can really
talk to you, you know?

01:56.650 --> 01:58.150
I get that a lot.
[ chuckles ]

01:58.152 --> 02:00.786
Actually,
I could use your help.

02:00.788 --> 02:01.987
I have a problem.

02:01.989 --> 02:03.889
You do?

02:03.891 --> 02:05.257
Though maybe you're not
the right person to ask.

02:05.259 --> 02:07.059
Try me.

02:07.061 --> 02:12.131
Well...I've been searching
forever, and...

02:12.133 --> 02:15.400
There was a cookie I had
once at a dinner

02:15.402 --> 02:16.735
With the president.

02:16.737 --> 02:18.170
A-a cookie?

02:18.172 --> 02:20.472
It was just to die --
I mean<i> really</i> to die.

02:20.474 --> 02:24.276
It was, oh, kind of cinnamon-y
but not spicy.

02:24.278 --> 02:26.345
I can't do spicy.
Of course not. [ scoffs ]

02:26.347 --> 02:28.080
And it had sugar on top

02:28.082 --> 02:30.282
And maybe just a little swirl
of caramel.

02:30.284 --> 02:32.751
I asked the chef,
but I forget what he called it.

02:32.753 --> 02:34.853
[ chuckles ]
it had a cute little name.

02:34.855 --> 02:37.156
Do you think you could
get me that recipe?

02:39.160 --> 02:41.527
I would<i> love</i> to.

02:41.529 --> 02:51.503
[ both laugh ]

02:51.505 --> 02:53.272
[ laughter ]

02:53.274 --> 02:55.207
Senator gibson,
gentlemen.

02:55.209 --> 02:56.642
Gibson: Mellie.

02:56.644 --> 02:58.510
Hope those special-interest
gifts are all under $50.

02:58.512 --> 03:01.113
I bought those
for my grandkids.

03:01.115 --> 03:03.448
Catching a flight home
just as soon as we, uh,

03:03.450 --> 03:05.184
Vote through
that spending bill.

03:05.186 --> 03:08.320
Which is the reason
for my visit.

03:08.322 --> 03:10.155
[ sighs ]
I found a mistake.

03:10.157 --> 03:11.657
Seems funding
for planned parenthood

03:11.659 --> 03:13.525
Has been put under
the discretionary column.

03:13.527 --> 03:16.495
Planned parenthood
will still be fully funded.

03:16.497 --> 03:20.299
True.

03:20.301 --> 03:22.000
But if it's moved
to discretionary,

03:22.002 --> 03:24.036
Then that money could be taken
away at any time,

03:24.038 --> 03:24.703
In future spending bills --

03:24.705 --> 03:26.171
It's funded.

03:26.173 --> 03:27.973
Nothing in this bill
says otherwise.

03:27.975 --> 03:31.910
But there's no guarantee,
and if there's no guarantee,

03:31.912 --> 03:35.013
Well, then
I can't vote for it.

03:35.015 --> 03:39.484
That bill will pass just fine
without you, mellie.

03:41.989 --> 03:45.824
I'm sure
there are others...

03:45.826 --> 03:49.561
When they find out,
they'll agree with me.

03:49.563 --> 03:51.597
I have never brought a bill
to the senate floor

03:51.599 --> 03:53.665
Without knowing how many votes
I need to pass it,

03:53.667 --> 03:55.500
And this one
is no exception.

03:55.502 --> 03:57.903
That's what makes me
so good at my job.

03:57.905 --> 04:00.872
And you know what's gonna make
you good at your job?

04:00.874 --> 04:03.442
Voting yes on this thing.

04:03.444 --> 04:05.677
Then we're all
gonna go home.

04:05.679 --> 04:08.380
Have ourselves
a merry little christmas.

04:08.382 --> 04:10.282
[ laughter ]

04:10.284 --> 04:12.084
[ chuckles ]
[ chuckles lightly ]

04:12.086 --> 04:13.852
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

04:13.854 --> 04:15.787
So this holiday dinner
for the cabinet,

04:15.789 --> 04:18.090
The social secretary wanted some
help with the place settings.

04:18.092 --> 04:20.359
Mitchell.
His name is mitchell.

04:20.361 --> 04:22.761
I know the schedule.
You don't need to tell me.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.529
I have a brain.

04:24.531 --> 04:27.399
Look, I know you hate this
stuff, but it's working.

04:27.401 --> 04:30.269
Our favorables are rising,
the country is accepting us,

04:30.271 --> 04:31.903
My funding bill
is gonna pass --

04:31.905 --> 04:33.605
[ quietly ]
crappy bill.

04:33.607 --> 04:36.041
What?

04:36.043 --> 04:37.809
Nothing.

04:39.980 --> 04:43.048
Huck, it's me -- again.

04:43.050 --> 04:44.216
I don't know if you're sick

04:44.218 --> 04:45.751
Or you're doing
your weird huck thing

04:45.753 --> 04:47.286
Where you disappear
for a while

04:47.288 --> 04:48.787
And come back like
nothing happened,

04:48.789 --> 04:51.023
But either way,
call me back.

04:52.593 --> 04:54.092
What is this?

04:54.094 --> 04:55.494
It's christmas.
Christmas?

04:55.496 --> 04:56.561
You don't have
to thank me.

04:56.563 --> 04:57.796
Oh, I wasn't going
to thank you.

04:57.798 --> 04:59.231
I was gonna tell you
to take this crap

04:59.233 --> 05:00.165
Out of here
before liv sees it.

05:00.167 --> 05:01.566
Liv hates christmas?

05:01.568 --> 05:04.136
Everybody over the age of 10
hates christmas.

05:04.138 --> 05:06.238
But everybody loves
a good holiday party.

05:06.240 --> 05:07.406
What'd you guys do
last year?

05:07.408 --> 05:08.440
Same as every year --

05:08.442 --> 05:09.908
We passed around
a bottle of vodka

05:09.910 --> 05:11.576
On the steps
of the lincoln memorial

05:11.578 --> 05:13.478
And went to work, because
that's what gladiators do.

05:13.480 --> 05:15.480
We don't...Decorate.
We work.

05:15.482 --> 05:16.882
Bah humbug.

05:21.622 --> 05:23.355
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

05:23.357 --> 05:24.690
Wait.
Before you go...

05:27.928 --> 05:28.760
What is this?

05:28.762 --> 05:30.095
Happy holidays.

05:30.097 --> 05:31.530
Sorry I didn't get a chance
to wrap it,

05:31.532 --> 05:32.964
But that was hard to do
with your hands down my pants.

05:32.966 --> 05:35.867
Keep it.
Come on.

05:35.869 --> 05:37.369
[<i> camera shutter clicks</i> ]

05:37.371 --> 05:38.804
[ scoffs ]

05:38.806 --> 05:40.105
Look, I get it --
you're embarrassed

05:40.107 --> 05:41.139
Because you didn't
get me anything.

05:41.141 --> 05:42.507
No.
No, you're not embarrassed,

05:42.509 --> 05:44.009
Or, no, you didn't
get me anything?

05:44.011 --> 05:46.211
I don't want
your bracelet, david.

05:46.213 --> 05:47.646
I just thought,
since we're doing this...

05:47.648 --> 05:49.381
"this"?

05:49.383 --> 05:50.716
...That I'd get you
something special,

05:50.718 --> 05:51.850
Because you are
someone special.

05:51.852 --> 05:52.951
'tis the season and all.

05:52.953 --> 05:55.053
If that isn't the saddest,
lamest...

05:55.055 --> 05:56.355
David...

05:56.357 --> 05:58.557
There's no need
for presents.

06:00.127 --> 06:01.426
Hope you kept
the receipt.

06:05.733 --> 06:07.833
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

06:07.835 --> 06:10.635
Senator gibson:
$1.1 trillion.

06:10.637 --> 06:13.071
Every penny stretched to within
an inch of its life.

06:13.073 --> 06:17.008
Wasn't easy, tell you that,
but we got it done.

06:17.010 --> 06:18.744
So, without further ado,

06:18.746 --> 06:21.413
'cause I know you all want to
get home to your families,

06:21.415 --> 06:23.715
I humbly suggest we put
this kitten to a vote.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.484
Mr. President?

06:25.486 --> 06:26.985
Thank you, senator.

06:26.987 --> 06:29.654
Is there anyone else who would
like to be recognized?

06:29.656 --> 06:31.990
No?
In that case --

06:31.992 --> 06:33.759
I'd like to be recognized.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.897
The chair recognizes the junior
senator from virginia.

06:38.899 --> 06:39.731
What the hell is this?

06:39.733 --> 06:41.933
[ senators murmuring ]

06:44.838 --> 06:46.338
So, here's the thing.

06:46.340 --> 06:49.508
This bill keeps the lights on,
and I'm all for that,

06:49.510 --> 06:52.043
Just not when it means
hurting people in the process.

06:52.045 --> 06:55.213
Mrs. Grant --
I have the floor.

06:55.215 --> 06:57.883
You say we're not defunding
planned parenthood,

06:57.885 --> 06:59.418
And technically you're right.

06:59.420 --> 07:01.386
But by making that money
discretionary,

07:01.388 --> 07:03.755
You give the people in this room
the power to say,

07:03.757 --> 07:06.291
"you know what? We're a little
over budget this year.

07:06.293 --> 07:09.060
How about we don't give that
little ladies' organization

07:09.062 --> 07:10.695
The full amount
they're asking for?"

07:10.697 --> 07:12.264
So you don't.

07:12.266 --> 07:15.901
And then, next year,
you give them even less,

07:15.903 --> 07:17.702
And even less
the year after that,

07:17.704 --> 07:19.905
And you keep chipping away
at their budget

07:19.907 --> 07:21.873
Until, before you know it,

07:21.875 --> 07:24.276
Planned parenthood
no longer exists.

07:26.213 --> 07:29.147
[ exhales sharply ]

07:29.149 --> 07:35.587
So, as much as I would like
to get home for the holidays,

07:35.589 --> 07:38.890
I refuse to do it at the expense
of women's health.

07:38.892 --> 07:40.492
So...

07:40.494 --> 07:41.893
Oh, no.

07:41.895 --> 07:43.428
...Before we vote,

07:43.430 --> 07:45.063
I'd like to tell you about

07:45.065 --> 07:47.065
The thousands of
federal projects

07:47.067 --> 07:48.667
That aren't discretionary...

07:48.669 --> 07:50.669
I don't believe this.
She's filibustering.

07:50.671 --> 07:52.938
...Like $5 million
we're spending

07:52.940 --> 07:55.273
On senate
hair-care services...

07:55.275 --> 07:56.441
Silence!

07:56.443 --> 07:58.076
...Or...
Senator grant has the floor.

07:58.078 --> 07:59.845
...The half a million dollars
it costs

07:59.847 --> 08:03.114
To paint an alaskan salmon
on senator campbell's 737.

08:03.116 --> 08:05.484
Not discretionary --
guaranteed.

08:05.486 --> 08:06.685
[ gavel bangs ]

08:06.687 --> 08:07.652
I said, quiet!

08:07.654 --> 08:10.489
A $25,000 travel stipend

08:10.491 --> 08:12.691
For the alabama
watermelon queen...

08:12.693 --> 08:14.493
[ senators grumbling ]

08:18.432 --> 08:20.165
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

08:20.167 --> 08:26.771
♪ chestnuts roasting
on an open fire ♪

08:26.773 --> 08:28.874
♪ jack frost
nipping at your nose ♪

08:28.876 --> 08:30.442
There aren't any
freedom fries.

08:30.444 --> 08:32.277
You got the underground railroad
without freedom fries.

08:32.279 --> 08:33.345
Who does that?

08:33.347 --> 08:36.548
♪ yuletide carols ♪

08:36.550 --> 08:38.683
♪ being sung by a choir ♪

08:38.685 --> 08:40.719
What is your plan here?

08:40.721 --> 08:42.454
What do you want?
You want something.

08:42.456 --> 08:44.122
I wouldn't be alive if you
didn't want something.

08:44.124 --> 08:46.558
You'd have, um...

08:46.560 --> 08:48.493
What's your thing?
Uh...

08:48.495 --> 08:50.061
Skinning!

08:50.063 --> 08:53.698
I'd be skinned
and eaten by now.

08:53.700 --> 08:56.668
So?

08:56.670 --> 08:57.802
♪ helps to make ♪

08:57.804 --> 09:00.171
♪ the seasons bright ♪

09:00.173 --> 09:02.641
You understand
I'm being generous?

09:02.643 --> 09:04.376
Kind?
♪ tiny tots... ♪

09:04.378 --> 09:05.844
I'm choosing kindness

09:05.846 --> 09:07.812
Because I need you
to understand

09:07.814 --> 09:09.247
I may be the bad guy,

09:09.249 --> 09:11.516
But the worse guys
are out there.

09:11.518 --> 09:13.318
I'm choosing kindness.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.587
♪ ...To sleep tonight ♪

09:15.589 --> 09:17.389
This is a rare moment.

09:17.391 --> 09:20.358
I'm allowing you
a little power here.

09:20.360 --> 09:24.229
If I were you,
I would make use of it, son!

09:24.231 --> 09:29.401
♪ he's loaded lots of toys
and goodies in his sleigh ♪

09:29.403 --> 09:32.904
You are no one's father,
and I am not your son.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.507
♪ ...Every mother's child... ♪

09:35.509 --> 09:39.277
Eat your underground railroad.
It's getting cold.

09:39.279 --> 09:46.418
♪ ...To see if reindeer
really know how to fly ♪

09:46.420 --> 09:51.022
♪ so, I'm offering... ♪
[ clatter ]

09:51.024 --> 09:53.558
<i> ...Before we vote,</i>
<i> I'd like to tell you</i>

09:53.560 --> 09:55.860
<i> About the thousands</i>
<i> of federal projects</i>

09:55.862 --> 09:57.429
<i> That aren't discretionary...</i>

09:57.431 --> 10:00.265
This the scene just hours ago
when mellie grant,

10:00.267 --> 10:03.134
The junior senator of virginia
and former first lady,

10:03.136 --> 10:05.971
Began her filibuster of
a congressional spending bill,

10:05.973 --> 10:08.540
A bill which, if it doesn't
pass by midnight,

10:08.542 --> 10:10.809
<i> Could lead to a very untimely</i>
<i> government shutdown.</i>

10:10.811 --> 10:12.611
It's never gonna
get that far.

10:12.613 --> 10:14.045
How can you be so sure?

10:14.047 --> 10:15.447
Because in order
to kill the bill,

10:15.449 --> 10:18.416
She has to stand up there
for 16 hours.

10:18.418 --> 10:21.219
That's 16 hours
where she's not allowed

10:21.221 --> 10:23.321
To lean on anything
for support,

10:23.323 --> 10:26.291
16 hours where she won't be able
to eat or pee.

10:26.293 --> 10:28.293
Yes, people have
done it before,

10:28.295 --> 10:30.328
But those people
trained for it.

10:30.330 --> 10:32.464
They put on diapers,
wear comfortable shoes...

10:32.466 --> 10:34.099
What do you think?

10:34.101 --> 10:36.601
There's no talking about mellie
without talking about you.

10:36.603 --> 10:38.837
If she looks desperate,
it's because you abandoned her.

10:38.839 --> 10:40.672
If she looks unstable,
it's because you kept her down

10:40.674 --> 10:42.107
All those years --
their words, not mine.

10:42.109 --> 10:44.175
I say we stay
far, far away.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.444
Watch her hang herself
by her own rope.

10:46.446 --> 10:48.146
I say we bring olivia in
to manage the message

10:48.148 --> 10:49.347
Outside the white house.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.016
Have her work some of
her media contacts.

10:51.018 --> 10:52.684
Olivia's busy.

10:52.686 --> 10:54.019
Can we make her un-busy?

10:54.021 --> 10:54.786
No.

10:54.788 --> 10:57.255
Okay.

10:57.257 --> 10:59.090
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

10:59.092 --> 11:00.959
38 million women
living in this country

11:00.961 --> 11:02.694
Are in need
of contraceptive care.

11:02.696 --> 11:05.530
20 million of those women
depend on government services

11:05.532 --> 11:07.198
To provide them birth control

11:07.200 --> 11:09.200
Because they are under
the age of 20

11:09.202 --> 11:11.770
Or are living below
the poverty line or both.

11:11.772 --> 11:14.773
But we're gonna have to say,
"sorry. We can't help you."

11:14.775 --> 11:16.941
And when they ask us why,
we can tell them.

11:16.943 --> 11:19.377
It's because we have
to allocate...

11:19.379 --> 11:22.847
$1.24 million for tree-snake
control in guam...

11:22.849 --> 11:26.284
Or [exhales sharply]

11:26.286 --> 11:29.220
$10,000 for talking
urinal cakes in michigan.

11:29.222 --> 11:33.158
$331,000 to study
"hangry" individuals.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.727
Not hungry, not angry --
hangry.

11:35.729 --> 11:38.196
Speaking of which...

11:39.966 --> 11:41.566
Point of order,
mr. President!
Shush!

11:41.568 --> 11:43.301
No, the --
the rules clearly state --

11:43.303 --> 11:44.402
The rules clearly state

11:44.404 --> 11:45.804
You cannot bring food
onto the floor.

11:45.806 --> 11:47.572
They say nothing about food
that is already here.

11:47.574 --> 11:51.743
The lady from virginia
is correct.

11:51.745 --> 11:53.411
Ahh.

11:53.413 --> 11:56.748
♪♪

11:56.750 --> 11:57.982
Where was I?

11:57.984 --> 12:01.419
Oh! Yes.

12:01.421 --> 12:06.624
$544,000 for the d.O.J.'s
premium linkedin account.

12:12.999 --> 12:14.099
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:17.504 --> 12:18.703
You're b613?

12:18.705 --> 12:20.839
Yes, sir.

12:31.885 --> 12:32.984
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:47.234 --> 12:49.968
Both:
"you can't take command, son!"

12:49.970 --> 12:51.736
He was the closest thing
to a father I ever had.

12:51.738 --> 12:53.404
Me too.

12:53.406 --> 12:54.806
<i> Where's rowan?</i>
<i> Why aren't you with him?</i>

12:54.808 --> 12:55.940
<i> Someone took him.</i>

12:55.942 --> 12:57.609
Tom:<i> Took him?</i>
<i> Where?</i>

12:57.611 --> 13:01.279
When you got out of prison,
what did we agree on?

13:01.281 --> 13:02.814
That rowan was a problem.
And?

13:02.816 --> 13:04.249
And that I was
to report to you,

13:04.251 --> 13:05.817
<i> Keep on eye on him.</i>

13:05.819 --> 13:07.719
<i> "keep an eye on him" --</i>
<i> that is all you had to do.</i>

13:07.721 --> 13:09.387
Now you're telling me
the only man

13:09.389 --> 13:11.289
That can stop lazarus
is...In the wind?

13:11.291 --> 13:13.091
<i> Find him.</i>

13:13.093 --> 13:14.325
Prove your worth.

13:14.327 --> 13:16.461
Give me a reason to let you
keep breathing.

13:19.132 --> 13:22.133
♪♪

13:29.910 --> 13:32.744
What's your question?

13:32.746 --> 13:34.679
You<i> are</i> good.

13:34.681 --> 13:37.182
But then,
